# Template drift allowlist for zudo-codemirror-wisdom.
# Generated projects start from create-zudo-doc templates; this file lists
# intentional divergences from the pinned create-zudo-doc baseline so
# `pnpm check:template-drift` exits 0.
#
# Format: one repo-relative path per line (no leading slash).
# Blank lines and `#` comments are ignored.
#
# Reconciled for the @takazudo/zudo-doc 4.2.1 "Minimal Scaffold" baseline. The
# v4 template file set that check:template-drift compares against is small:
#   base:    pages/index.tsx, pages/docs/[[...slug]].tsx,
#            scripts/setup-doc-skill.sh, src/styles/global.css, tsconfig.json
#   i18n:    pages/[locale]/docs/[[...slug]].tsx
# pages/index.tsx, scripts/setup-doc-skill.sh, and tsconfig.json are kept
# byte-identical to the v4 templates (no entry needed).
#
# NOTE: this repo's CodeMirror domain (scripts/cm6-bundle-entry.ts,
# scripts/build-cm6-bundle.sh, public/assets/cm6-bundle.min.js, the
# settings.htmlPreview.head injection, and the window.CM demo MDX) is NOT
# template-owned, so it never appears in the drift check and needs no entry here.

# ── docHistory-patched doc-route stubs ────────────────────────────────────
# The docHistory feature patches both doc catch-all route stubs to statically
# import DocHistory and merge it into the chrome bindings. The generator emits
# this patched form (present in a fresh v4 scaffold with docHistory on), but the
# UNPATCHED base/i18n templates ship without the DocHistory wiring, so the drift
# check flags them. These are the scaffolder's own patched output.
pages/docs/[[...slug]].tsx
pages/[locale]/docs/[[...slug]].tsx

# ── Host customization: brand typography (Futura) + Noto body font ────────
# src/styles/global.css re-applies the --font-noto / --font-futura brand tokens,
# points --font-sans at Noto, and adds the [data-header-logo] + h1.text-heading
# Futura rules on top of the regenerated v4 base global.css.
src/styles/global.css

# ── Wide home page override (css-wisdom PR #182 parity) ──
# pages/index.tsx is reconstructed (no longer the locked 1-line re-export) to
# render HomePageView with `wide`, matching the zudo-doc showcase. See the
# file header + upstream toggle request zudolab/zudo-doc#2959.
pages/index.tsx
